translated: Björkman, Astrid Carola, senior physician, Vänersborg, born January 9th, 1886 to pharmacist Karl B. and Matty Egerström. She completed her studentexamen in Stockholm in 1904, followed by her medical and philosophy degree in Uppsala in 1906, and her medical degree in 1910. She received her medical license in Stockholm in 1917. She served as a medical intern at Uppsala epidemic hospital in 1912, Säters hospital and Uddevalla county hospital, and was appointed as a prosectorial physician in Borgholm from 1917 to 1919. From 1919 to 1925, she was a resident physician at Lund's hospital, after which she was promoted to second-class resident physician from 1925 to 1927. She was then promoted to first-class resident physician at Helsingborg's hospital from 1927 to 1930, and acting senior physician at Källshagens hospital in Vänersborg in 1930. From 1931 to 1936, she served as a senior physician of first class and hospital director at Källshagens hospital, and continued on in this position at Restads hospital in Vänersborg from 1936 onward. She married but the name of her partner and the date of marriage is unknown.
